\Pr\{X+Y<t\} \le \Pr\{X<t\} \Pr\{Y<t\}
X
Y
X(\omega)+Y(\omega)<t
X(\omega)\geq 0
Y(\omega)<t
Y(\omega)\geq 0
X(\omega)<t
\{X+Y<t\}\subset \{X<t\}\cap \{Y\cap t\}
X
Y
P(\{X+Y<t\})\leq P(\{X<t\}\cap \{Y<t\})=P(\{X<t\})\cdot P(\{Y<t\}).
\mathbb{P}(X+Y< t)=\int_{0}^{t}\mathbb{P}(Y< t-u)\mathbb{P}(X\in du).
\{Y< t-u\}\subset\{Y< t\}
\mathbb{P}(Y<t-u)\leq \mathbb{P}(Y<t).
\mathbb{P}(X+Y< t)\leq\mathbb{P}(Y< t)\int_{0}^{t}\mathbb{P}(X\in du)=\mathbb{P}(Y< t)\mathbb{P}(X< t).
